<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-08.S2W-17478.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0708.htm#5">Mental Health</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-08.S2W-17478.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80116" speakername="Stewart Stevenson (Banff and Buchan) (SNP)" spid="S2W-17478" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0708.htm#5">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how many staff members were attacked with weapons in mental health wards in each of the last five years.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-08.S2W-17478.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80064" speakername="Lewis Macdonald" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0708.htm#5">

  <p>Information on the number of attacks on mental health wards is not held centrally. The information available on violence is published on the Scottish Health Statistics website under Workforce Statistics, <a href="http://www.isdscotland.org/workforce" target="_blank">www.isdscotland.org/workforce</a> .</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-08.S2W-17466.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0708.htm#6">School Transport</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-08.S2W-17466.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80000" speakername="Brian Adam (Aberdeen North) (SNP)" spid="S2W-17466" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0708.htm#6">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether it will consider supporting US-style yellow school buses as part of its anti-congestion measures.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-08.S2W-17466.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80097" speakername="Peter Peacock" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0708.htm#6">

  <p>The Executive supports moves to reduce traffic congestion. Use of buses, including dedicated school buses, is one of a number of options which the Executive would be prepared to consider to encourage safer, healthier and more sustainable travel to school. However, statutory responsibility for school transport rests with education authorities.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-08.S2W-13459.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0708.htm#7">Scottish Executive</minor-heading>

